hackathon-description-text: Final Project Submissions for ESE111, Atoms, Bits, Circuits and Systems.
hackathon-eligibility: You need to be enrolled in ESE111 at UPenn
hackathon-rules:
You can upload the content (video, final abstract) until 5P on 12 Dec 2014. 
The content must include your name(s) and Title of your project.

hackathon-prizes.prize-content: There will be 3 prizes for the best project and each team member will get a Pebble watch

hackathon-location-google-maps: https://maps.google.com/?q=University of Pennsylvania, Philadelphia, PA 19104, USA

hackathon-judging-criteria.judging-criterion: Grade from 1-5 based on how the product was presented, description of potential market and overall quality.
Grade 1-5 based upon quality and efficacy of prototype implementation.
Grade from 1-5 based on video showing final demonstration and description.
Grade from 1-5 based on the written content and technical documentation on their project submission page.
